vrpr — license attribution
==========================

The `vrpr` package is distributed under the MIT license.

It vendors (under `src/vendor/pyvrp/`) the C++ core of the PyVRP project
(https://github.com/PyVRP/PyVRP), also under the MIT license, © PyVRP contributors.
The exact vendored version is recorded in `tools/PYVRP_VERSION` and in
`src/vendor/pyvrp/pyvrp_version.txt`.

The R <-> C++ binding layer (`src/*.cpp` outside `vendor/`), the R code in `R/`, and
the documentation are © vrpr authors, under the same MIT license.

See `inst/COPYRIGHTS` for the detailed copyright breakdown and LICENSE.md for the
full MIT license text.
